<!-- 11: STATES -->
<div class="dt-section">
  <div class="dt-section-header">
    <span class="dt-section-number">11</span>
    <h2 class="dt-section-title">States: empty, loading, error, no results</h2>
  </div>

  <p class="dt-text">
    A table has four states beyond happy-path data, and two of them are constantly confused. The empty state (no data yet) explains why the table is empty and offers a primary action to add the first record. The no-results state (after filtering to zero rows) is different: it must say the filters matched nothing and offer a one-click Clear filters. Loading prefers skeleton rows that mirror the real column layout over a bare spinner, with the region marked <code>aria-busy="true"</code> while it loads. On error, keep any stale data visible under an error banner with a retry rather than blanking the screen.
  </p>

